What is the entry point of an application?
>> an application runs the main method is its entry point.
Why main is static?
>>Main method is static because only then it can be invoked by runtime engine without creating an object

What is the difference between an Interface and Abstract class?
>>Interface only declears method and variables without any definition and the classes which
 will be use those should implement those methods .On the other side abstract class must have at
 least one abstract  method which will defined in the child class. it can also have non abstract method
 but we can not create an instance of an abstract class.

Can you make an Object from an Interface and Abstract class ? if not how do you use it ?

>>>No , we can't . But we can implement interface and extend abstract class and then create new concrete class.
we can create objects of the concrete class.
what is Access Specifier?
>>Acccess specifier determines which variables or methods or class can be accesed by which user.
