>>When we have same method name and two different parameters then we have to use overload
What is method overriding and when it happens?
>>If we want to modify a method of parent class we use overriding we can redefine the method in child
class
Explain exceptions in java and how to handle it.
>> An exception is an event, which occurs during the execution of a program,
 that disrupts the normal flow of the program's instructions. It can be handled throwing exceptions
 or using try/catch method.
What is static keyword in java? How it has been used in variables and methods ?
>>Static means the following properties after static keyword is part of the class not object;
Static in terms of variable: We can assign static variable without creating an object
Static in terms of methods: We can use the static method of a class without creating an object of that
class.

What is final and how it has been used variables and methods?
>>Final makes the variable constant means that its value cannot be changed later.
And final methods mean those methods cant be overidden

What is final, finally and finalize?
>> Final is keyword to make a class variable or method constant
Finally used in try catch block to close the block
Finalize is method which is invoked for garbage collection to remove the instance which are not refer
anced.
