What is heap?
>>Heap is part of memory management system where instance of classes is saved

How java manage it's memory?
>>Java object resides in an area called the heap. The heap is created when the JVM starts usp and may
increaswe or decrease in size while the applications runs . When the heap becomes full, garbage is collected
by java gabage collector.During this process, objects that are no longer used are cleared , thus
makes new space for new objects

>>String is prototype of text
Stringbuffer is mutable means one can change the value of the object.The object created through
StringBuilder is stored the heap.String Buffer has the same methods as the StringBuilder. but each
method in stringbuffer is synchronized that is Strign buffer is thread safe.

strintbuilder: String builder is same as the StringBuffer, that is it stores the object in heap and
it can also be modified. The main difference between the StringBuffer and stringBuilder is the String
builder is also not thread safe.
